---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Use Plain Language and Concrete Examples"
  description="Avoid technical jargon and abstract concepts. Use everyday language and specific examples that users can relate to."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Plain language explanations" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full">
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Plain Language Explanation</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            ><b>Why this email was flagged:</b> It asks you to click a link and enter your password, which
            is a common sign of phishing. The sender's email address doesn't match the company it claims
            to be from (it says "PayPal" but comes from "paypal-security@random-domain.com").</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Uses concrete examples (clicking links, entering passwords) and specific details (email
            mismatch) that users can understand and verify.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-status-error-10 border border-status-error-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/error" class="text-status-error-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"><b>Technical Jargon (Unhelpful)</b></mds-text>
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >This message was classified as malicious based on anomaly detection algorithms
            analyzing feature vectors including lexical patterns, domain reputation scores, and
            behavioral heuristics. The classification confidence threshold exceeded 0.87.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-error-06"
            >Uses technical terms (anomaly detection, feature vectors, lexical patterns) that don't
            help users understand why the email is suspicious or what they should do.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Concrete Example</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            ><b>Example:</b> Instead of saying "the model identified semantic similarity," say "these
            two documents discuss the same topic: both are about renewable energy policies."</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Provides a concrete example that shows what "semantic similarity" means in practical
            terms.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Use everyday language and specific examples that users can relate to.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Use technical jargon, acronyms, or abstract concepts without explanation.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Show concrete examples of what the AI output means in practice.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">Assume users understand technical terms or AI/ML concepts.</UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
